abstract: More than 2,000 people protesting potential cuts to the national health care system staged a sit-in on Westminster Bridge in London.
snippet: More than 2,000 people protesting potential cuts to the national health care system staged a sit-in on Westminster Bridge in London.
lead_paragraph: More than 2,000 people protesting potential cuts to the national health care system staged a sit-in on Westminster Bridge in London on Sunday afternoon, blocking traffic on one of the city's busiest bridges, The Guardian reports.

headline.main: 2,000 Stage Sit In on a London Bridge to Protest Health Care Cuts
